---
import PageLayout from '../../../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const relatedLogs = (await getCollection('en/log', ({ data }) =>
  data.published !== false && data.project_tag === 'AutoTrading'
)).sort((a, b) => b.data.date.getTime() - a.data.date.getTime());

const relatedInsights = (await getCollection('en/insight', ({ data }) =>
  data.published !== false && data.project_tag === 'AutoTrading'
)).sort((a, b) => b.data.date.getTime() - a.data.date.getTime());
---

<PageLayout title="AI Auto-Trading Experiment" description="An experiment building and running an automated trading system with AI and ₩5M. No code written by hand — just rules, an AI assistant, and real capital on the line.">
  <div class="project-detail">
    <a href="/en/projects" class="back-link">← Projects</a>

    <div class="project-header">
      <span class="project-status status-active">🟢 Live</span>
      <h1>AI Auto-Trading Experiment</h1>
      <p class="project-meta">Current version: <strong>v1.2</strong> · Last updated: <strong>2026-04-14</strong></p>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>An experiment building and running an automated trading system with AI and ₩5M.<br>
      A non-coder handles judgment; AI handles execution. That collaboration structure is the core.</p>
      <p>The goal isn't profit.<br>
      The goal is the experience of building a system where AI operates real capital — by hand.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Current Position</h2>
      <p>2026-04-14. First live order filled. DRY_RUN validation complete — switched to live.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Collaboration Structure</h2>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Role</th><th>Owner</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Strategy direction + situation assessment</td><td>Meta-Chulbuji (GPT)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Code analysis + execution</td><td>Claude Code</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Direction setting + final judgment</td><td>Operator (Chulbuji)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Current Strategy</h2>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Buy signal</td><td>RSI (Wilder) 40–65</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Trend filter</td><td>Within 5% of MA20</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Position size</td><td>20% per ticker / max ₩1,000,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Take-profit</td><td>+6% fixed or trailing stop</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Trailing stop</td><td>Activates at +4% / sells at −2% from peak</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Stop-loss</td><td>−3%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Same-day rebuy</td><td>Blocked</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>2026.04.14 Update — Live Transition Complete</h2>
      <p>DRY_RUN validation finished; system switched to live. Three fixes before market open, operational additions in the afternoon.</p>

      <h3>✅ STEP 6 — RSI Wilder method + MA20 5% deviation cap</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>RSI method switch</td><td>Previous method → Wilder smoothing</td></tr>
          <tr><td>MA20 deviation cap</td><td>Block buy if price &gt;5% above MA20 (prevents chasing highs)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>✅ STEP 7 — Trailing stop introduced</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Activation condition</td><td>Trailing activates when gain reaches +4%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Sell condition</td><td>Sell when price drops −2% from peak</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>✅ STEP 8 — Cash balance fallback logic</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Fallback handling</td><td>Covers cash balance query failure on unexpected API response</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>✅ STEP 9 — Operational additions</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Trailing activation log</td><td>Real-time visibility into which tickers hit the threshold</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Post-market Telegram summary</td><td>Automatic portfolio position report after close</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Scheduler --live flag</td><td>Automated live trading starts tomorrow</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p><strong>End-of-day results:</strong> Samsung Electronics +1.60% / Kakao −0.41% / Total portfolio ₩10,002,370</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>2026.04.10 Update — Production-Grade Structural Overhaul Complete</h2>
      <p>This wasn't patching a few lines of code. It was building the infrastructure needed to run an automated trading system reliably. Direction and situation assessment handled by Meta-Chulbuji; actual code analysis, fixes, and verification handled by a specialized dev AI and Claude Code. 11 items overhauled in two hours yesterday evening.</p>

      <h3>✅ Stability Fixes</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Cash balance field replacement</td><td>Wrong field reference → replaced with correct field</td></tr>
          <tr><td>API retry logic</td><td>Added retry structure on call failure</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Duplicate buy prevention</td><td>Block duplicate buys on the same ticker</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Duplicate process prevention</td><td>Prevent multiple scheduler instances from running</td></tr>
          <tr><td>hold_days bug fix</td><td>Fixed error in position holding day calculation</td></tr>
          <tr><td>IS_PAPER safety guard</td><td>Prevent paper/live mode cross-contamination</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>✅ Strategy Refinements</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>RSI Wilder method</td><td>Previous method → switched to Wilder smoothing</td></tr>
          <tr><td>RSI range adjustment</td><td>Adjusted to 40–65</td></tr>
          <tr><td>MA20 deviation cap</td><td>Added condition: within 5% of MA20</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Investment allocation expanded</td><td>20%, up to ₩1,000,000 per position</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Trailing stop introduced</td><td>First implementation of profit-zone protection</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>✅ Operations Structure</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Buy scan structure</td><td>1× pre-market + 4× intraday</td></tr>
          <tr><td>DRY RUN / LIVE separation</td><td>Clearly distinguished in logs and Telegram</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Post-market summary</td><td>Automatic daily operations summary</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Verification checkpoint</td><td>Monday first-run checklist defined</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>How Operations Work Now</h2>
      <p>This update established the collaboration structure for the project going forward.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>With Meta-Chulbuji</strong> — direction, situation assessment, strategy prioritization</li>
        <li><strong>With specialized dev AI</strong> — code analysis, fixes, verification, implementation</li>
      </ul>
      <p>From chasing each bug myself to focusing on direction and judgment. Dividing the roles changed the pace.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What's Next</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>STEP 10: Add volume surge condition</li>
        <li>STEP 11: Migrate ticker universe to .env</li>
        <li>Review adding sector-diversified tickers</li>
        <li>Establish live account switchover SOP</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Update History</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>2026-04-14 · v1.2</strong> — Live transition complete. STEP 6–9: trailing stop refinement / cash balance fallback / post-market Telegram summary / first live order filled (Kakao 20 shares @ ₩48,350)</li>
        <li><strong>2026-04-10</strong> — Production-grade structural overhaul: cash balance field fix / API retry logic / duplicate buy & process prevention / hold_days bug fix / IS_PAPER safety guard / RSI Wilder method / RSI range 40–65 / MA20 deviation 5% cap / allocation 20% up to ₩1M / trailing stop introduced / operations collaboration structure redesigned</li>
        <li><strong>2026-04-09</strong> — Python module cache issue identified — confirmed in live operation that code changes are not reflected without restarting the scheduler. Added diagnostic logs to is_market_ok() / MA60 fallback to close &gt; MA20 for paper trading environment applied / same fallback applied to check_buy_signal() / BUY reason string format error fixed / DRY_RUN buy cycle restored / scheduler restart SOP document created</li>
        <li><strong>v1.1</strong> · 2026-04-08 — Dual regime filter / ₩10B volume filter / IMMEDIATE·NEXT_OPEN sell branching / same-day rebuy block / log system overhaul</li>
        <li><strong>v1.0</strong> · 2026-04-07 — KIS API, rule engine, Telegram alerts, scheduler MVP complete</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Related Logs</h2>
      {relatedLogs.length > 0 ? (
        <ul class="related-list">
          {relatedLogs.map(post => (
            <li>
              <a href={`/en/log/${post.slug}`}>{post.data.title}</a>
              <span class="post-date">{post.data.date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'short', day: 'numeric' })}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      ) : (
        <p class="placeholder">No related logs yet.</p>
      )}
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Related Insights</h2>
      {relatedInsights.length > 0 ? (
        <ul class="related-list">
          {relatedInsights.map(post => (
            <li>
              <a href={`/en/insight/${post.slug}`}>{post.data.title}</a>
              <span class="post-date">{post.data.date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'short', day: 'numeric' })}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      ) : (
        <p class="placeholder">No related insights yet. Add <code>project_tag: "AutoTrading"</code> to any insight file to link it here automatically.</p>
      )}
    </section>
  </div>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .project-detail {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    color: #1976d2;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .project-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .project-header h1 {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 2rem;
  }

  .project-status {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .status-experimental {
    background-color: #fce4ec;
    color: #c62828;
  }

  .status-active {
    background-color: #e8f5e9;
    color: #2e7d32;
  }

  .project-meta {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
  }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section p {
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .placeholder {
    color: #999;
  }

  .section ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .section ul a {
    color: #1976d2;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .section ul a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .related-list {
    padding-left: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .related-list li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .related-list a {
    color: #1976d2;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .related-list a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .post-date {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #888;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .section h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  .update-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #444;
  }

  .update-table th {
    background-color: #f5f5f5;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .update-table td {
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .update-table tr:nth-child(even) td {
    background-color: #fafafa;
  }
</style>
